### Description

A Deconstruction Statement in a service subscription stops build of Angular project.  I have spent several hours testing that this code is valid in Repl.it for both JavaScript and TypeScript.

My code without object Deconstruction compiles fine:

```
 this.data.getScore(this.titleUrl).subscribe(data => {
  this.avgRating=data['avgrating'];
  this.numReviews=data['numOfReviews'];
  this.posterUrl = data['posterUrl']'  
``` 
     


My code with either object Deconstruction below throws an error:

```
 this.data.getScore(this.titleUrl).subscribe(data => {
  ({avgrating: this.avgRating, numOfReviews: this.numReviews, posterUrl: this.posterUrl}= data) 
```
     


```
this.data.getMovieInfo(this.titleUrl).subscribe(({id, title, poster_url, backdrop_url}) => {
        this.title=title;
        this.posterUrl=poster_url;
        this.backdropUrl=backdrop_url;
```
The errors I get back are:

ERROR in src/app/app.component.ts(84,11): error TS2459: Type 'Object' has no property 'poster_Url' and no string index signature. 

I have tested this in multiple ways to try a workaround with Destructuring this but all have failed even though almost exact code can be reproduced in Repl.it with either javascript or typescript and it passes.  
 It seems the bug is the fact that the compiler doesn't know what is on the data object as it is coming from my BackEnd API even though I do know what will be on the object and refuses to build.

